node.text: Here I am 1 month after bringing Maya into the world 🌎 I started to implement dance and movement back into my days very slowly. The natural breech baby birth is challenging for the body so I’m taking it easy. I must say that the power of dance is often underestimated. Not only it provides physical exercise that you can choose to be light or very straining, it also provides mental exercise for creativity and emotional and social support due to music and people around you. We often talk with my husband about the fact how dance is the perfect cure to a lot of things. I would be draining in baby blues which is a type of afterbirth anxiety and mood swings but I believe that thanks to dance I’m able to keep myself well enough. Fun facts: No matter if I take 3 showers a day, the postpartum hormonal sweat is like “please Jesus help me” hahaha. Also even 5 meals a day is not enough, I’m always hungry after breastfeeding on demand, plus I could drink a well of water 😅 @slimboogie777 chest is the perfect place for Maya’s nap ❤️

node.text: Here’s super simple way on how to make your own vanilla extract at home that is 💯 better, higher quality, efficient, cheaper and healthier than store bought. Many times you don’t even know that the vanilla extract you buy at the store is not real let alone the vanilla products are not real. Ughhhhh 😩 with this one you can bake, make ice cream, shakes, make your own lotion, shampoo, conditioner, whatever you would like !

• 
• how to practice 
• what is practice 
• why do we practice 
• life, dance and practice 
• tips, ideas, perspectives 

The topic of today’s live talk was practice. We exchanged different opinions and perspectives about practice not only relating to dance but life. This is a topic we talk a lot about in our home and with our friends and students so we wanted to share a little bit with you all. We hope you enjoy it. Much love ❤️ @slimboogie777

node.text:
During pregnancy I still kept:
• being completely plant based 🌱 with the exception of @apricotlanefarms eggs once in a while 
• doing @iceman_hof breathing techniques every day with shorter retention times to make sure I’m being careful 
• meditating every day and learning new breathing techniques 
• dancing and practicing every day, even if it was for 30 mins
• sessioning with dance friends
• traveling
• exercising and stretching especially my pelvic, hips and legs 
• teaching up to 18 classes a week, rescheduling my classes when I needed a break and planning to keep teaching until labor 
• bike riding, hiking, swimming with my love 
• I stopped jogging because it felt uncomfortable 
• doing every day normal life stuff, being active 
• but also taking naps every day even if it was 10 mins 
• 👩🏼‍🤝‍👨🏽❤️👶🏼

node.text: Hi everyone, we just wanted to send love to everyone who blessed us with amazing gifts for our baby Maya. We really appreciate you ❤️ family, friends, fans from all over the world showed us so much support. Much love from me & @slimboogie777 👩🏼‍🤝‍👨🏽 We are so excited about this journey! If we have forgotten to include someone’s name, we apologize, but you are in our thoughts. There was so much love coming our way ❤️

node.text: Something that I have been reflecting a lot on recently 👉🏻 Little do we realize that we aren’t really connecting with the people around us at all, only what we project onto them, which is merely our own idea of them, we feel close to them. However, the moment our idea of the other doesn’t work for them, the feeling of closeness ends 📚 read it again, tell me what you think after observing it 💭 enjoy this vibe with my loves @slimboogie777 & Maya 👶🏼 almost 9 months in• 🎶 @ma2t___

node.text: I’m not sure if the fact that it’s Maya who’s getting all the hype now is making me more happy or the fact that I was still able to do this throughout the whole pregnancy. What the human body can do is incredible and the most amazing thing is that we are meant to do this. Often times pregnancy is looked at with fear or as a disability, but what I’m feeling personally is empowerment. It’s actually making my practice and dance so much more aware because I had to stop using my core and relearning all of these styles without core is pure practice on being in the present moment, letting go of the ego and connecting with the intuition. If I was to listen to the doctors, I would be on antibiotics right now, destroying mine and babies microbiome for something that absolutely does not need the attention of antibiotics, and something that was simply solved with herbs plus in their opinion I would not be exercising and dancing which was ultimately the thing that made me feel the best alongside keeping plant based lifestyle. Doctors are great in emergency situations, don’t get me wrong, but in every day life, they put extreme amount of fear into peoples brains that effect us so much which ultimately isn’t even their fault but the systems doing. We as humans should be striving more for research, education, different perspectives, books and connection with our intuition again. Believing in our doing and our observations more, believing in ourselves and our values.

node.text: She’s been having eating troubles causing her a lot of bloating. She has absolutely no control over what she eats and snacks on throughout the day and night. She’s been having a lot of pain in her stomach caused by the bloating. She likes to blame it on her husband that fills up the fridge every day, she likes to blame it on her friends parties full of food, she likes to blame it on Uber Eats that gives her discounts every day for delivery, she likes to blame it on the government that is allowing to sell cheap food in fast food chains, she likes to blame it on food commercials, she likes to blame it on not having enough time to cook healthy meals or she likes to blame it on her culture being a certain way and she loves to play victim to all of these excuses. Her reality is heavily manipulated, food has complete control over her every day even through she thinks she has control over her own life. She’s not willing to be aware of it, put in research, work, dedication and effort. She spends money on expensive work out props like boxing bag and bikes that she never ends up using. Then she ends up treating everyone around her with poor quality actions the same way she treats herself. The root of her troubles stems from her parents feeding her cookies every time she was sad, angry or when she cried while she was a child. Her parents unconsciously build a toxic pattern into her life. Now she doesn’t know how to accept these feelings in a healthy way without overeating.• 🎵 @thriftworks

node.text: Here I am 1 month after bringing Maya into the world 🌎 I started to implement dance and movement back into my days very slowly. The natural breech baby birth is challenging for the body so I’m taking it easy. I must say that the power of dance is often underestimated. Not only it provides physical exercise that you can choose to be light or very straining, it also provides mental exercise for creativity and emotional and social support due to music and people around you. We often talk with my husband about the fact how dance is the perfect cure to a lot of things. I would be draining in baby blues which is a type of afterbirth anxiety and mood swings but I believe that thanks to dance I’m able to keep myself well enough. Fun facts: No matter if I take 3 showers a day, the postpartum hormonal sweat is like “please Jesus help me” hahaha. Also even 5 meals a day is not enough, I’m always hungry after breastfeeding on demand, plus I could drink a well of water 😅 @slimboogie777 chest is the perfect place for Maya’s nap ❤️

node.text: Story time 👉🏻 I’ve been making transition into being plant based since 2016, pescatarian, vegetarian, vegan, alkaline whole food plant based, raw vegan 🌱 I was making a transition because of health issues. Not only I was able to get rid of cervical cancer cells in situ, alongside that it also got rid of all of my injuries, inflammations in my body from dance and traveling, I stopped being sick, I’ve had headache since 2017 three times only, my body recovery is much faster now, even recovery from covid last year while being pregnant was very easy with whole food plant based lifestyle. When me and my husband first got together he ate fast food western diet mainly including all kinds of processed foods, meats, dairy. When we started to talk about having a baby, he actually told me that he doesn’t believe he’s capable of having a child because of his last experiences and also encounters with doctors and what they have told him. I was also at risk for possibly having complications because of my past health conditions. We both knew we wanted to have a baby and my husband was open minded enough to give it a try and change his eating lifestyle completely. He was capable of going vegan from one day to another and keep it up. I was impressed. He even tried the raw veganism with me. I also started to give him some herbs and minerals such as sarsaparilla, burdock root, seamoss and fertility support herb blend. Our pregnancy tests was coming out negative for 3 months at first while on this transition and I was starting to get stressed. So my husband told me to stop taking the tests and just let it flow. Couple weeks later I suddenly felt change in my body, it was instant, I remember it and then I was late on my monthly cycle. I remember coming out of the bathroom with a positive test and we both couldn’t believe it at first, we were so happy ❤️ I’m sharing this story because after this we met many people that can not conceive but they actually never thought of changing their eating lifestyle. So in hopes that this might actually help someone and change their life like it changed ours 🥰 @slimboogie777 #plantbasedpregnancy

node.text: We are totally in love with this bundle of joy 😍 Maya is very peaceful, calm, observing, likes to do things her own way already. Fun fact: since day 1 we are meditating and doing @iceman_hof Wim Hof breathing techniques together already. I just put her on my chest to let her feel the energy and she gets super calm with it. She also loves to watch daddy dance @slimboogie777

node.text: Me and my husband agreed on one thing “We never knew true love until we met Maya” connecting us with such a powerful spell, we fell even deeper in love with each other and with Maya ❤️ it’s incredible, it’s amazing, it’s beautiful, it’s breathtaking. There are no words for it. Every time I look at them cuddling and kissing together I cry, literally… @slimboogie777 you are truly the best partner, husband, lover and support. Seeing you entering fatherhood is so special. Fun fact ☺️ I asked my husband to put Maya on his chest first when Maya is born. It was special and important moment for me to witness.

node.text:
When people asked us when is our due date, we never said it to anyone. We believe it puts unnecessary pressure on the brain and the baby. We trusted that Maya will decide herself when is a good time to come into the world. We decided to do home birth because we wanted to bring our baby girl into this world naturally, unmedicated and without interruptions. We felt unnecessary fear, lack of education and unnecessary medical interventions from all 3 clinics we’ve visited. Home birth was the absolute best decision. Our original due date from our amazing midwives was July 10th, I took a guess that Maya will come July 9th on a cancer new moon. July 9th 7:30 am it was like a wake up call. I went straight into regular contractions lasting 45 seconds 3 minutes apart that were getting more and more intense every time. First thing, I started to clean the house 😆, then me and my love danced 💃🏼 , then I called my parents, and at 10:20 am my water broke. It was fast ! The midwives were rushing to our place because first time moms are usually taking their time however Maya was ready. Around 11:15 am I completely left this world, trying to focus on hypno birthing techniques and traveling in between extreme intense pain and incredibly amazing out of this universe feelings at the same time. I was in this most intense phase for about a hour when we realized that Maya was a surprise breech!!! She wasn’t coming head first, but her booty first which required completely different birthing position out of the water. My mind went into a warrior superwomen level right away. The CRAZY part is that if Maya didn’t hide it so well that she was breech, I would have been taken into hospital for c section right away because California doesn’t allow breech natural birth ! Everything happened for a reason WOW! I was so thankful we didn’t find out about her being breech earlier. She was born at 1:05 pm happy, healthy and so precious.
My love @slimboogie777 you are the best most supportive man I could ever ask for ❤️ and thank you @birthingrhythm @laboroflovela @kindredspacela for being the best team of midwives ! There’s no words that could truly express this incredible experience !

node.text: Here’s super simple way on how to make your own vanilla extract at home that is 💯 better, higher quality, efficient, cheaper and healthier than store bought. Many times you don’t even know that the vanilla extract you buy at the store is not real let alone the vanilla products are not real. Ughhhhh 😩 with this one you can bake, make ice cream, shakes, make your own lotion, shampoo, conditioner, whatever you would like !
